workflow Flowline Pre-Release Readiness
runner codex

agent inspect-workflow-engine
title Inspect workflow DSL and runtime
prompt Inspect README.md, src/workflow.coil, prompts/create-workflow.md, and workflows/refund.flow. Review parsing, dependency resolution, concurrent readiness, agent launching, output capture, catalog refresh, approval handling, and the documented DSL limits; report concrete release blockers, risks, and supporting file references. Do not modify files.
after none

agent verify-native-build
title Verify native build and checks
prompt Inspect Coil.toml, src/main.coil, src/workflow.coil, and src/raylib.coil, then run coil build, ./flowline --check-workflow, and ./flowline --check-catalog from the repository root. Report exact commands, exit results, structured check output, Raylib linkage or asset failures, and any release blocker; do not change source files.
after none

agent review-interface-behavior
title Review Raylib interface behavior
prompt Inspect README.md, src/main.coil, and src/raylib.coil. Trace AppState and InputFrame transitions through workflow selection, run requests, node inspection, creation modal input, approval, resizing, and rendering; assess whether visible behavior matches the documented interface and report concrete usability or correctness risks with file references. Do not modify files or launch the graphical application.
after none

agent combine-technical-evidence
title Combine engine and build evidence
prompt Read .flowline/node0.output and .flowline/node1.output produced by this run. Reconcile the workflow-engine review with native build and CLI evidence, identify contradictions or missing verification, and return a concise technical go or no-go assessment with blockers. Do not modify files and do not draft a release summary.
after inspect-workflow-engine, verify-native-build

agent prepare-approval-evidence
title Prepare approval evidence
prompt Read .flowline/node2.output and .flowline/node3.output produced by this run. Check that interface findings and technical evidence are complete enough for a human release decision, then list only unresolved blockers, material risks, and missing evidence. Do not modify files and do not draft a release summary.
after review-interface-behavior, combine-technical-evidence

approval approve-release-summary
title Approve release summary preparation
after prepare-approval-evidence

agent prepare-release-summary
title Prepare release summary
prompt Human approval to prepare the release summary has been granted. Read .flowline/node0.output, .flowline/node1.output, .flowline/node2.output, .flowline/node3.output, and .flowline/node4.output from this run, then produce a concise pre-release summary covering workflow DSL and runtime findings, native build and CLI results, interface behavior, blockers, residual risks, and a final go or no-go recommendation. Do not modify files or publish a release.
after approve-release-summary
